      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Here is a draft for your rejection email. It should be professional, kind, and clear about the final decision. You can adapt it to sound like your own voice, but remember to keep the tone genuinely appreciative, even though the news is disappointing.\n\nSubject: Update on the Senior Developer Role at [Company Name]\n\nDear [Candidate Name],\n\nThank you so much for investing your time and energy into the final rounds for the Senior Developer position. We were truly impressed with your strong grasp of system design and the excellent cultural alignment you demonstrated during our conversations. This was an incredibly difficult decision, as we had several highly qualified candidates. However, we have decided to move forward with another candidate whose specific experience was a slightly closer match for our immediate needs at this time.\n\nWe sincerely wish you the very best in your job search and future endeavors.\n\nBest regards,\n\n[Your Name]",
